Since you didn't specify a package manager, here is the "Gold Standard" .gitignore for a modern Python/FastAPI project. It covers everything from standard virtual environments to newer tools like Poetry and Ruff.

The Essential FastAPI .gitignore
Ini, TOML
# --- Python Basics ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# --- Environments (Crucial) ---
.env
.venv
env/
venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/

# --- Dependency Managers ---
# If using Pipenv
*.pipflow
# If using Poetry (ignore the virtualenvs, NOT the pyproject.toml/poetry.lock)
.virtualenvs/

# --- Fast API & Pydantic ---
.pydantic_ai_cache/
.pyre/

# --- Testing & Coverage ---
.target/
.pytest_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.cover
htmlcov/
.hypothesis/

# --- Linting & Typing ---
.mypy_cache/
.dmypy.json
dmypy.json
.pyre/
.ruff_cache/
.typeguard_cache/

# --- Databases (SQLite / Local Data) ---
*.db
*.sqlite3
/data/

# --- IDEs & Editors ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
